  "text": "The Firefox Servo-based CSS style system resolution pipeline in layout/style/ consists of the following key files:\n\n1. **ServoStyleSet.h** (`layout/style/ServoStyleSet.h`) — Header declaring the `ServoStyleSet` class, which is the main C++ entry point for style resolution, backed by a Servo Stylist. It contains the static `Current()` method and `IsInServoTraversal()` check, and is a friend of `RestyleManager`.\n\n2. **ServoStyleSet.cpp** (`layout/style/ServoStyleSet.cpp`) — Implementation of `ServoStyleSet`, including constructor/destructor and all style resolution methods.\n\n3. **ServoBindings.h** (`layout/style/ServoBindings.h`) — The Gecko-to-Servo FFI declarations header. It declares `extern \"C\"` functions via macros (e.g., `Servo_StyleSet_StyleRuleChanged`, `Servo_CssRules_Get*RuleAt`, `Servo_CounterStyleRule_GetDescriptorCssText`) that allow Gecko C++ code to call into the Servo Rust style engine.\n\n4. **RestyleManager.h** (`layout/style/RestyleManager.h`) — Header for `RestyleManager`, the component that schedules and manages style recalculation. It defines `ServoRestyleState` (a stack class for passing restyle state) and `RestyleManager` (which holds a reference to `ServoStyleSet` and the `nsStyleChangeList`).\n\n5. **ServoUtils.h** (`layout/style/ServoUtils.h`) — Utility header for Servo traversal state. Declares `InitializeServo()`, `ShutdownServo()`, `AssertIsMainThreadOrServoFontMetricsLocked()`, and the inline `IsInServoTraversal()` function that checks the `sInServoTraversal` global pointer.\n\n6. **moz.build** (`layout/style/moz.build`) — The build configuration file for `layout/style/` that lists all style system source files and headers, including `ServoBindings.h`, `ServoStyleSet.h`, `ServoStyleSet.cpp`, `RestyleManager.h`, `ServoUtils.h`, and many others."
}

